---
description: Repo-wide policy — no AI attribution in commits, PRs, or anything else that lands in version-control history.
alwaysApply: true
---

Do not add any AI authorship attribution to anything that lands in version-control history. This includes:

- `Co-Authored-By: Claude ...` (or any other AI model) trailers in commit messages
- "🤖 Generated with Claude Code" / "Generated by Cursor" lines in commit messages or PR descriptions
- "Written by AI" / "Generated by ..." comments inside source files
- AI-involvement mentions in branch names, PR descriptions, release notes, or changelog entries

Author the work as the user. This applies to every commit, PR, branch, and code comment regardless of how it was produced.
